[32m│[0m 2. GraphQL introspection exposed the full schema, revealing the hidden `flag` field                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. The `getPrescriptions` query accepts any `userId` parameter without authorization checks                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. No authentication required to query GraphQL endpoint directly                                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **How Filters/Security Controls Behaved**:                                                                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Session cookie required for `/view_prescriptions` UI page                                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - But GraphQL endpoint accessible without authentication                                                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - No server-side validation that the requesting user owns the requested userID                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - GraphQL introspection enabled (should be disabled in production)                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **IDOR Vulnerability Confirmed**:                                                                                                                    [32m│[0m
